WEBVTT

00:01.936 --> 00:04.169
Ohh, yeah!

00:04.171 --> 00:06.839
♪ Powerpuff girls
fighting crime ♪

00:06.841 --> 00:09.108
♪ To save the world
before bedtime ♪

00:09.110 --> 00:11.477
♪ Here's the time to shine
when you're fighting crime ♪

00:11.479 --> 00:13.512
♪ Power it up ♪
♪ Who's got the power? ♪

00:13.514 --> 00:14.980
♪ We got the power ♪

00:14.982 --> 00:17.182
♪ Breaking through the wall,
gonna do it all ♪

00:17.184 --> 00:19.385
♪ We don't quit ♪
♪ Who's got the power? ♪

00:19.387 --> 00:21.020
♪ We got the power ♪

00:21.022 --> 00:23.756
Oh! Yeah!

00:28.749 --> 00:31.183
[ Birds singing ]

00:31.185 --> 00:33.185
[ School bell rings ]
[ All cheering ]

00:33.187 --> 00:34.786
[ Sniffs, sighs ]

00:34.788 --> 00:36.054
You smell that, girls?

00:36.056 --> 00:38.190
-I didn't do it!
-Wasn't me.

00:38.192 --> 00:42.060
No, I'm talking about
the smell of spring!

00:42.062 --> 00:43.528
Spring!

00:43.530 --> 00:45.097
Oh, yeah!

00:45.099 --> 00:46.765
[ Wind whistles ]

00:46.767 --> 00:48.266
Speak for yourselves.

00:48.268 --> 00:50.135
That makes another winter
come and gone

00:50.137 --> 00:51.770
without a single snow day.

00:51.772 --> 00:55.073
You can't be down in springtime
because...

00:55.075 --> 00:57.075
♪ It's spring, it's spring ♪

00:57.077 --> 00:58.743
♪ spring is in the air ♪

00:58.745 --> 01:00.445
♪ birds are chirping,
bees, they buzz ♪

01:00.447 --> 01:02.314
♪ the fresh breeze
through my hair ♪

01:02.316 --> 01:04.249
♪ accountants doing taxes ♪

01:04.251 --> 01:06.418
♪ and flowers everywhere ♪

01:06.420 --> 01:07.886
Oh!

01:07.888 --> 01:10.822
Hey, Blossom.

01:10.824 --> 01:12.757
♪ Butterflies ♪
♪ I love ya ♪

01:12.759 --> 01:15.293
♪ ooh, ooh, ooh ♪
♪ I need ya ♪

01:15.295 --> 01:17.129
Hello, Jared Shapiro,
uh...

01:17.131 --> 01:19.264
[ Clears throat ]
...Casual friend.

01:19.266 --> 01:21.399
-I got you these.
-Uh...

01:21.401 --> 01:23.135
Hey, Blossom,
your face is all red.

01:23.137 --> 01:25.170
Are you feeling okay?
'Cause your face is red.

01:25.172 --> 01:28.907
Why is your face all red?
[ Laughs ]

01:28.909 --> 01:31.343
[ Laughs harder ]

01:31.345 --> 01:34.179
I also wanted
to give you this.

01:34.982 --> 01:37.482
[ Laughs nervously ]

01:37.484 --> 01:38.984
Whoo!

01:38.986 --> 01:40.118
Bubbles: "I like you.

01:40.120 --> 01:43.021
Do you like me, too?
Yes or no?"

01:43.023 --> 01:45.290
Ooh!

01:45.292 --> 01:47.025
You have to say something!

01:47.027 --> 01:49.294
What are you gonna say?
What's your answer?!

01:49.296 --> 01:52.531
It's okay, you can tell me
your answer tomorrow.

01:52.533 --> 01:53.999
[ Laughs ]

01:54.001 --> 01:56.334
Huh?
Okay, bye.

01:57.871 --> 01:59.504
Tomorrow?

01:59.506 --> 02:00.705
[ Echoing ]<i> Tomorrow...</i>

02:00.707 --> 02:03.008
<i> Tomorrow...</i>
<i> Tomorrow...</i>

02:03.010 --> 02:04.509
Blossom?

02:04.511 --> 02:05.477
You okay?

02:05.479 --> 02:07.646
Let Dr. Buttercup
get this.

02:07.648 --> 02:09.814
Hey, Bloss, how many fingers
am I holding up?

02:09.816 --> 02:11.283
[ Tink! ]
Two.

02:11.285 --> 02:13.218
Well, she's still
counting okay,

02:13.220 --> 02:15.554
which means she's probably okay
to hear this.

02:15.556 --> 02:16.888
[ Clears throat ]

02:16.890 --> 02:19.558
Blossom's got a boyfriend!
Blossom's got a boyfriend!

02:19.560 --> 02:22.227
Blossom's got a boyfriend!
Blossom's got a boyfriend!

02:22.229 --> 02:23.728
I do not!

02:23.730 --> 02:27.032
What's the matter?
Don't you like Jared?

02:27.034 --> 02:29.634
I do like him.
I just...

02:29.636 --> 02:32.137
What if I check yes?
What happens?

02:32.139 --> 02:33.471
It's simple.

02:33.473 --> 02:35.540
You get married,
and you're together forever

02:35.542 --> 02:39.511
and ever and ever
and ever and ever and ever!

02:39.513 --> 02:41.813
She's totally right.
It's scientific fact.

02:41.815 --> 02:44.649
♪ Blossom and Jared
sittin' in a tree ♪

02:44.651 --> 02:48.386
-♪ k-i-s-s-i-n-g ♪
-♪ k-i-s-s-i-n-g ♪

02:48.388 --> 02:50.021
[ Horse whinnies ]

02:50.023 --> 02:51.323
Blossom, darling!

02:51.325 --> 02:52.724
Jared, dearest!

02:52.726 --> 02:54.893
What do you think
of my latest novel?

02:54.895 --> 02:56.261
Sincerely?

02:56.263 --> 02:58.230
'Tis your best work yet!

02:58.232 --> 03:00.232
It's already won
tons of awards.

03:00.234 --> 03:02.234
And you've been made
queen president

03:02.236 --> 03:04.669
of all the yearbook clubs
forever!

03:04.671 --> 03:07.405
And...I love you.

03:07.407 --> 03:11.176
Announcer:
<i> A new novel, out today.</i>

03:11.178 --> 03:13.745
[ Gasps ]
That was the best dream ever!

03:13.747 --> 03:17.015
But there's no guarantee he'll
be that supportive in real life!

03:17.017 --> 03:18.917
Ugh! I cant face Jared!

03:18.919 --> 03:20.352
I can't go to school today!

03:20.354 --> 03:24.456
Stop your sleep-yakkin', Bloss.
Look!

03:24.458 --> 03:26.758
Snow day!
Snow day! Snow day!

03:26.760 --> 03:28.526
No school!
No school! No school!

03:28.528 --> 03:32.364
Too bad you won't be able
to see your boyfriend today!

03:32.366 --> 03:35.533
Yeah. Too bad.

03:35.535 --> 03:38.837
All right! Time to take on
Fitzmaurice Hill!

03:40.540 --> 03:43.108
Announcer:<i> Sleddie!</i>

03:43.110 --> 03:45.410
<i> Monsieur death!</i>

03:45.412 --> 03:47.612
<i> Old Betty, classic.</i>

03:47.614 --> 03:51.483
Okay, ladies. Last one down
buys the hot chocolate.

03:51.485 --> 03:52.317
Whee!

03:52.319 --> 03:54.219
Hey, not until I say "go!"

03:54.221 --> 03:55.654
Go? Okay!

03:55.656 --> 03:58.290
Does no one respect
the time-honored traditions

03:58.292 --> 04:01.760
of competitive sledding?!

04:01.762 --> 04:03.395
Whee!

04:04.798 --> 04:06.965
Nice sled, old-school.

04:06.967 --> 04:08.733
But how's it handle?

04:10.570 --> 04:11.569
Not bad!

04:11.571 --> 04:14.139
I hope
that's not all you have.

04:14.141 --> 04:16.608
[ All cheering, laughing ]

04:16.610 --> 04:18.476
-Whoo-hoo! Yeah!
-Yeah, buddy!

04:18.478 --> 04:21.813
-Here we go!
-This is really fun!

04:21.815 --> 04:25.283
I want my hot chocolate
with extra whipped -- bunnies?

04:25.285 --> 04:27.152
Weird. Bunnies!

04:27.154 --> 04:28.153
[ Ding! ]

04:28.155 --> 04:29.187
Whoa!

04:29.189 --> 04:31.489
Whoa-aah-aah-aah!

04:31.491 --> 04:33.391
Bunnies!
[ Squeak! ]

04:34.795 --> 04:36.361
Yay!

04:36.997 --> 04:40.532
Okay! Maybe a little help here,
old-school?

04:40.534 --> 04:42.967
I have one more move
for you!

04:42.969 --> 04:44.769
Ice breath?!

04:44.771 --> 04:48.006
♪♪

04:48.008 --> 04:50.342
Yay!
Whoo! Whee!

04:52.779 --> 04:54.312
Whoo-hoo!
Whoo-hoo! Whoo-hoo!

04:54.314 --> 04:56.514
I'll take a large hot chocolate,
please.

04:56.516 --> 04:57.515
Me, too.

04:57.517 --> 05:00.752
Okay, okay,
hot chocolate is on me.

05:01.555 --> 05:03.955
Bummer about
all the snow melting.

05:03.957 --> 05:07.025
Totally. I guess
it's back to school tomorrow.

05:07.027 --> 05:08.059
Jared?

05:08.061 --> 05:10.028
[ Echoing ]
Jared? Jared?

05:10.030 --> 05:11.830
Your hot cocoa is ready.

05:11.832 --> 05:12.864
Oh, super.

05:12.866 --> 05:14.399
Thanks. Yummers.

05:14.401 --> 05:17.235
Oh, no! I'm not ready
to give him my answer!

05:17.237 --> 05:19.070
I need more time!
[ Yelping in pain ]

05:19.072 --> 05:21.039
Careful,
that drink is hot.

05:21.041 --> 05:23.742
♪♪

05:23.744 --> 05:26.478
One more snow day
couldn't hurt.

05:30.584 --> 05:32.717
Announcer:
<i> Snow watch -- day 30.</i>

05:32.719 --> 05:35.420
Well, Bob,
it's another cold one out here,

05:35.422 --> 05:37.322
and to make matters worse,

05:37.324 --> 05:39.858
Townsville has been overrun
by Yetis!

05:39.860 --> 05:42.227
Announcer:
<i> Yeti watch -- day one.</i>

05:42.229 --> 05:43.728
You're telling me, Nick.

05:43.730 --> 05:46.598
They seem to be attracted
by all the snow.

05:46.600 --> 05:48.566
And what brings you
to Townsville?

05:48.568 --> 05:51.736
Mm-yes.
This place is just so charming,

05:51.738 --> 05:53.905
the perfect winter resort.

05:53.907 --> 05:55.907
Ugh, so true, darling.

05:55.909 --> 05:58.910
The Matterhorn<i> wishes</i>
it were this place.

05:58.912 --> 06:00.412
Whoa! Yetis.

06:00.414 --> 06:01.746
Yetis?!

06:01.748 --> 06:04.182
Forever snow,
and now Yetis?!

06:04.184 --> 06:06.918
I'm sure they're really great
once you get to know them.

06:06.920 --> 06:08.420
I'm sick of the snow!

06:08.422 --> 06:11.256
It's been a month,
and I'm just gonna say it!

06:11.258 --> 06:12.524
I kind of miss school.

06:12.526 --> 06:15.293
Me, too.
My brain is getting all mushy

06:15.295 --> 06:17.962
and, uh, uh...Not usey.

06:17.964 --> 06:21.433
I do miss the smell of used
textbooks in the morning.

06:21.435 --> 06:22.867
Oh, yeah, Blossom.

06:22.869 --> 06:25.136
You must really be bummed
about all this snow.

06:25.138 --> 06:28.807
You haven't seen your boyfriend
since he asked you out!

06:28.809 --> 06:29.641
Yeah!

06:29.643 --> 06:31.576
He is not my boyfriend!

06:31.578 --> 06:33.578
And...I love the snow!

06:33.580 --> 06:35.280
Don't you love the snow?

06:35.282 --> 06:36.915
Let's go sledding!
I love sledding!

06:36.917 --> 06:39.784
Sledding in the snow's
the best!

06:39.786 --> 06:42.787
I think the snow
is going to her head.

06:42.789 --> 06:45.924
Hey! What happened
to Fitzmaurice Hill?

06:45.926 --> 06:47.625
A Yeti ski resort?

06:47.627 --> 06:50.862
[ Yetis chuckling politely ]

06:53.600 --> 06:54.966
-Ugh.
-Poor people.

06:54.968 --> 06:58.236
So our hill's
been overrun by Yetis?

06:58.238 --> 06:59.938
I'm sure it's fine,
Buttercup.

06:59.940 --> 07:01.739
There's plenty of room
for all of us.

07:01.741 --> 07:03.508
Oof!
[ Muffled techno music playing ]

07:03.510 --> 07:06.911
Sorry, there isn't
plenty of room for you.

07:06.913 --> 07:09.013
You're gonna have to
get off the mountain.

07:09.015 --> 07:10.482
It's a Yeti resort now.

07:10.484 --> 07:13.184
Oh, yeah?!
Well, I'm gonna<i> resort</i>

07:13.186 --> 07:15.787
to kicking your butt,
furball!

07:15.789 --> 07:18.656
No, Buttercup,
it's not worth it.

07:18.658 --> 07:21.025
We'll find someplace else
to sled.

07:21.027 --> 07:22.494
[ Growls ]

07:23.630 --> 07:25.897
[ Chuckles ]
Tiny people.

07:26.833 --> 07:29.501
Man, I hate
these snobby Yetis!

07:29.503 --> 07:30.802
I wish
they'd all just go back

07:30.804 --> 07:32.804
to whatever snowball
they came from.

07:32.806 --> 07:35.673
Yeah, I wish
we could get rid of this snow.

07:35.675 --> 07:39.310
Then maybe they'd leave,
and we can bring spring back.

07:39.312 --> 07:42.580
♪♪

07:45.552 --> 07:48.286
I wish I could
bring spring back, too.

07:48.288 --> 07:50.321
[ Breathes deeply ]

07:50.323 --> 07:51.356
Ahem?

07:51.358 --> 07:53.224
[ Coughs ]
Oh.

07:53.226 --> 07:55.493
That was supposed to be
a personal moment.

07:55.495 --> 07:57.862
Blossom!
It was you the whole time?!

07:57.864 --> 08:01.399
We thought it was the effects
of climate change!

08:01.401 --> 08:03.201
I-i didn't want to.

08:03.203 --> 08:06.538
I was just so nervous about
answering Jared Shapiro's note,

08:06.540 --> 08:09.541
and I needed extra time
to think about it, so...

08:09.543 --> 08:11.976
I made the snow day
last a little longer.

08:11.978 --> 08:13.211
A month?!

08:13.213 --> 08:14.879
But you guys
like the snow.

08:14.881 --> 08:17.181
It's a win-win
for everyone.

08:17.183 --> 08:19.183
And the Yetis?!

08:19.185 --> 08:21.052
I'm sorry!

08:21.054 --> 08:24.322
But, honestly,
the Yetis may be annoying,

08:24.324 --> 08:25.990
but they are not monsters.

08:25.992 --> 08:29.494
[ Zack roaring ]

08:29.496 --> 08:30.995
Whoo-hoo!

08:32.399 --> 08:34.165
[ Grunting ]

08:34.167 --> 08:35.667
[ Car alarm blaring ]

08:35.669 --> 08:38.136
[ Continues grunting ]

08:40.840 --> 08:43.508
Ugh. I guess it was only
a matter of time

08:43.510 --> 08:45.076
before Zack showed up.

08:45.078 --> 08:48.613
Tell me about it.
That guy ruined the Matterhorn.

08:48.615 --> 08:50.181
[ Laughing ]

08:50.183 --> 08:51.516
Oh, no!

08:51.518 --> 08:53.885
Hey!
Quit destroying our town!

08:53.887 --> 08:57.255
This ain't your town anymore!
This is<i> our</i> town!

08:57.257 --> 09:00.191
[ Grunts ]

09:00.193 --> 09:01.659
[ Inhales deeply ]

09:03.396 --> 09:04.729
You made all this happen

09:04.731 --> 09:07.198
because you were scared
of your boyfriend?!

09:07.200 --> 09:08.433
[ Grunts ]

09:08.435 --> 09:12.070
Yo, that's cold!

09:12.072 --> 09:13.571
Hold that thought.

09:13.573 --> 09:15.039
[ Inhales deeply ]

09:17.110 --> 09:20.144
Freezing Townsville
is no way to solve the problem.

09:20.146 --> 09:21.913
Ice eventually melts.

09:21.915 --> 09:24.816
[ Growls ]

09:24.818 --> 09:27.452
You need to face your problems
head-on!

09:27.454 --> 09:28.786
[ Growling ]

09:28.788 --> 09:31.389
It's time to take care
of business, Bloss!

09:31.391 --> 09:33.491
I know. But, guys!

09:33.493 --> 09:34.559
[ Growling ]

09:34.561 --> 09:36.761
No more ice breath!

09:36.763 --> 09:38.296
Yeah!
[ Growling ]

09:38.298 --> 09:39.631
But --

09:39.633 --> 09:42.100
-no more ice breath!
-No more ice breath!

09:42.102 --> 09:42.800
[ Inhales sharply ]

09:46.573 --> 09:49.474
Except that time.
That time was good.

09:49.476 --> 09:51.609
Okay, girls, you're right.

09:51.611 --> 09:53.678
Time to take care of business.

09:53.680 --> 09:55.313
[ Grunts ]

09:55.315 --> 09:57.315
[ Grunts ]

09:59.019 --> 10:00.251
[ Ting! ]

10:00.253 --> 10:01.619
[ Sighs ]

10:01.621 --> 10:05.790
This place just became
another Matterhorn.

10:05.792 --> 10:08.793
[ Indistinct conversations ]

10:08.795 --> 10:12.463
[ Clarinet playing ]

10:12.465 --> 10:13.765
Hey, Jared.
[ Sour note plays ]

10:13.767 --> 10:15.366
Uh -- uh -- oh.

10:15.368 --> 10:17.335
H-hey, Blossom.

10:17.337 --> 10:19.637
Can I...Talk to you?

10:19.639 --> 10:21.005
Uh -- uh, sure.

10:21.007 --> 10:23.474
Did you get a chance
to think about my note?

10:23.476 --> 10:24.676
Uh...

10:24.678 --> 10:26.144
[ Inhales deeply ]

10:26.146 --> 10:28.179
I thought the note you gave me
was very sweet.

10:28.181 --> 10:30.148
And while I think
that you're really great,

10:30.150 --> 10:32.350
and some may even say
i have a crush on you,

10:32.352 --> 10:33.518
I've given it much thought.

10:33.520 --> 10:35.186
And after consulting
those closest to me,

10:35.188 --> 10:38.022
I've concluded that I'm just not
ready for a relationship.

10:38.024 --> 10:39.624
Is that okay?

10:39.626 --> 10:40.858
Oh, uh...

10:40.860 --> 10:43.361
I'm not ready
for a relationship, either.

10:43.363 --> 10:45.196
I just think you're neat.

10:45.198 --> 10:47.498
Oh! Uh...Ditto!

10:47.500 --> 10:49.133
[ Both laugh nervously ]

10:49.135 --> 10:51.369
Hey, you want
to grab a snow cone?

10:51.371 --> 10:55.339
Oh, man, I think I've had
enough snow for a while.

10:55.341 --> 10:56.374
[ Both chuckle ]

10:56.376 --> 10:58.376
Ooh!

10:58.378 --> 11:01.212
How romantic!

11:05.218 --> 11:06.884
♪ Powerpuff girls
fighting crime ♪

11:06.886 --> 11:09.487
♪ saving the world
before bedtime ♪

11:09.489 --> 11:12.323
♪ battling evil toe-to-toe ♪

11:12.325 --> 11:16.227
♪ saving the day,
a powerpuff goal ♪
